<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 18px;">Basic VIM Commands</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">#: Written by KFH: </span><a href="mailto:karshi.hasanov@utoronto.ca" style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">karshi.hasanov@utoronto.ca</a></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">#: Date: Sept. 20, 2001</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">#: Description: The short list of commands I use often</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">#: Last Modified: April 1, 2018</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">#: Changes: Removed the some and added some.</span></div><div><br /></div><div>Hint: You can go to a specific line number while opening a file:</div><div> <span style="font-weight: bold;">vi</span> +<span style="color: rgb(148, 55, 255);">line_number </span><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);"> </span><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255); font-style: italic;">filename.txt</span></div><div> <span style="font-weight: bold;">vi +</span><span style="color: rgb(148, 55, 255);">15 </span><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255); font-style: italic;">sshd_config</span></div><div><hr /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">DELETE text(s)</span> </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">dw</span>    - delete a word ( from the current position to the end of the word)</div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">D </span>    - delete from the current position to the end of the current line </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">ndd </span>  - delete  n - lines </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">dG</span>    - delete from the current position to the end of the file </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">d1G</span>    - delete from the current position to the beginig of the file </div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">&lt;Shift&gt; + </span><span style="font-weight: bold;">d </span> -<span style="font-weight: bold;"> </span>delete characters from the current position to the end of a line?</div><div><br /></div><div><hr /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">UNDO editing: </span> </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">u </span>      - undo the last command </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">U </span>      - undo the current line from all changed made on that line </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">:e! </span>    - edit again ( restarts to the state of the last save) </div><div><hr /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">MOVING cursor around: </span></div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">G</span>    - go to the end of the fil</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;"> 1</span><span style="font-weight: bold;">G</span>  - go to the beginning of the file</div><div> <span style="font-weight: bold;">n</span><span style="font-weight: bold;">G</span>  - go to <span style="font-weight: bold;">n </span>-th line</div><div>   </div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">0 </span>-  move the cursor to the beginning of the current line</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">$ </span>-  move the cursor to the end of the current line</div><div><b>w</b> - move the cursor to the<font color="#008f00"><b> righ</b>t </font>by a “<font color="#9437ff">word</font>"</div><div><b>b</b> - move the cursor to the <font color="#942193"><b>left</b></font> by a  “<font color="#9437ff">word</font>”</div><div>   </div><div><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);"># “H” , “J” “K” ,”L”  ( All small letters)</span></div><div>"<span style="font-weight: bold;">h</span>” (Left)  "<span style="font-weight: bold;">j</span>” (Down) "<span style="font-weight: bold;">k</span>” (Up) "<span style="font-weight: bold;">l</span>” (Right)</div><div><hr /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">CUT, COPY and PAST</span></div><div>   Note: You can use the DELETE options to CUT and then PAST with "pp" or "P" as shown below</div><div>   "<span style="font-weight: bold;">yy</span>"   - copy a current line</div><div>   "<span style="font-weight: bold;">nyy</span>"  - copy "n" lines (including the current line)</div><div>   "<span style="font-weight: bold;">yw</span>"   - copy a word</div><div>   "<span style="font-weight: bold;">y$</span>"   - copy from the current position to the end of the line</div><div>   "<span style="font-weight: bold;">y1G</span>"  - copy all lines from the current to the BEGINNING of the file</div><div>   "<span style="font-weight: bold;">yG</span>"   - copy all lines from the current to the END of the file</div><div>   "<span style="font-weight: bold;">p</span>"   - past below the current file</div><div>   "<span style="font-weight: bold;">P</span>"    - past above the current line</div><div><hr /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">SEARCH and REPLACE</span></div><div><b><font style="font-size: 18px;">:/</font></b><i><font color="#009193">word</font>  </i>- search for <font color="#009193"><i>word</i></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">:/</span>  </font>        - search again the same  <span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147); font-style: italic;">word</span></div><div> <span style="font-weight: bold;">r</span>     - replace a character under the cursor</div><div> <span style="font-weight: bold;">nr</span>   - replace "n" characters from the current position   </div><div> <span style="font-weight: bold;">:</span><b><font color="#941100">%</font><font color="#ff2f92">s</font></b>/<font color="#4f8f00">search</font>/<font color="#0433ff">replace</font>/<b>g     </b>      <span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);"># Research and replace , "</span><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);">g</span><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);">" - mean all in the file</span></div><div> <span style="font-weight: bold;">:</span><b><font color="#941100">%</font><font color="#ff2f92">s</font></b>/<font color="#4f8f00">search</font>/<font color="#0433ff">replace</font>/<b>gc</b>         <span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);"> #Research and replace , "</span><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);">c</span><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);">" - mean confirm first</span></div><div><hr /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">SHOW LINE NUMBERS</span> </div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">:set </span>number  or <span style="font-weight: bold;">:set</span> nu</div><hr /><div> <span style="font-weight: bold;">SAVE and EXIT</span></div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">:w!</span> ,  <span style="font-weight: bold;">:q!</span> , <span style="font-weight: bold;">:wq</span> </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">:w </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0); font-style: italic;">new_file_name</span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> </span>   <span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);"># Save as a "new_file_name</span></div><div><hr /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">SPLIT SCREEN</span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">:sp</span>     - horizontally split</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">:vsp </span>  - vertically split</div><div># To jump from one Window to an other:</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">&lt;Control&gt;</span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> ww</span>  ( twice “w”)</div><div><hr /><b>HINTS</b><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">TO JUMP</span> (between closing parenthesis, square brackets, curly braces <b><font color="#ff2f92">{</font></b><font color="#0096ff">…</font><b><font color="#ff2f92">}</font></b> )</div><div><font color="#008f00">%</font><span style="font-weight: bold;"> </span> - brings the cursor to the matching position .</div><div>        For example, if your your cursor is on</div><div>          the top of "<font color="#ff2f92"><b>{</b></font>" and you press "<b>%</b>" it will put the cursor on "<b><font color="#ff2f92">}</font></b>" or reverse versa.    </div><div><br /></div><div><hr /></div><div>